            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> good idea! ci failure though\r\n\r\nCI is failing because of the 3rd commit. Basically require'vim.ui' is failing and pcall doesn't seem to catch the error. Probably cause vimruntime isn't set right/lua module loader is acting up somewhere. Since vim.ui is lazy loaded, If we just check package.loaded['vim.ui'] then unless something else triggers vim.ui it doesn't get loaded and the progress status doesn't get displayed.",
